  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this pilot study is to develop the methodology for an innovative subsurface
      imaging technology that was designed at Lawrence Livermore National Laboratory. It will allow
      the non-invasive analysis and imaging of tissues and chemical distributions in the body at an
      imaging depth of up to 1 centimeter with spatial resolution on the order of 1 mm.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This is a pilot, feasibility study to determine if the subsurface imaging technology warrants
      advancement to a larger clinical trial.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
